\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. R. elephas} (L.) Griseb., {\i Spicil. Fl. Rumel.} {\b 2}: 12 (1844). Stems up to 50 cm, erect or ascending, more or less branched subglabrous. Leaves 10-30 × 5-15 mm, obovate to elliptical shallowly crenate-serrate, obtuse, rounded to subcordate at base, glabrous; petioles 4-8 mm. Lower bracts like the leaves, the upper smaller, ovate, sessile; pedicels 4-8 mm. Corolla 10-15 mm, yellow; beak 6-10 mm, straight. Capsule suborbicular.{\i  Mountain grassland. S. Italy, Sicilia; Balkan peninsula from C. Greece to C. Bulgaria}. Bu Gr It Si.
