\pard\f0\fs28\qc {\b 38.                  Cymbaria}                L.
\par

\pard\f0\fs28\qc (incl. {\i Cymbochasma} (Endl.) Klokov & Zoz)
\par

\pard\f0\fs24\qc By D.A. Webb.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Perennial herbs, somewhat woody at the base, with undivided, opposite leaves. Flowers solitary, axillary, bracteolate. Calyx equally 5-lobed. Corolla with obconical tube and 2-lipped limb; lips subparallel, the upper entire, cucullate, the lower 3-lobed. Stamens 4, didynamous, somewhat exserted from upper lip of corolla. Stigma capitate. Capsule loculicidal; placentae large, 2-lobed; ovules numerous; seeds few.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. C. borysthenica} Pallas ex Schlecht. in Nees,{\i  Horae Phys. Berol.} 109 (1820) ({\i Cymbochasma borysthenicum} (Pallas ex Schlecht.) Klokov & Zoz). Whole plant silvery-sericeous to greyish-villous. Stems 3-15 cm, simple, erect from a branched, woody stock. Leaves 5-20 × 1-3 mm, linear-lanceolate, acute, entire. Flowers few, in axils of lower leaves; pedicel 1-2 mm; bracteoles overlapping the calyx-tube. Corolla 25-35 mm, pale yellow; tube longer than lips. Seeds elliptical, flat, winged. {\i Steppes and other dry places. • S. Ukraine, just extending to S. Russia}. Rs (W, E).
\par

