\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. L. rhodopea} Dingler, {\i Bot. Zeit.}{\b  35}: 74 (1877). Like {\b 1} but up to 50 cm; whole plant yellowish-brown; raceme not secund, usually longer and denser than in {\b 1}; pedicels 1-2 mm; calyx 5-7 mm; corolla c. 10 mm, with upper lip slightly cucullate; seeds few.{\i  Parasitic on the roots of various trees. • S. Bulgaria, N.E. Greece.} Bu Gr.
